          <pubDate>Wed, 08 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
          <author>Unknown</author>
          <link>https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/mum-portrait/</link>
          <guid>https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/mum-portrait/</guid>
          <description xml:base="https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/mum-portrait/">



&lt;img alt=&quot;Mum&quot; title=&quot;Mum&quot; src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;mum.5e7ca6ec735a1f9b.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;mum.ad84733ef83aa3d3.webp 512w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;mum.5e7ca6ec735a1f9b.webp 1024w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;mum.a5a1d852763c66eb.webp 2048w&quot; class=&quot;The finished picture&quot; &#x2F;&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#x27;ve spent the last 4 sessions at art painting course working on a portrait of my mum. It&#x27;s her birthday today and I&#x27;ll give her it tonight. It&#x27;s another big piece, similar size to the painting I did of Neil just before Christmas. I&#x27;m pleased with how this came out, I would have liked another 2 hour session to tidy up some of the areas that I feel a little unresolved but that always seems to be the case with my oil paintings!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;




&lt;img alt=&quot;Mum&quot; title=&quot;Mum&quot; src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;progress.5ee7b919931734ae.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;progress.cadeadb580e5da2d.webp 512w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;progress.5ee7b919931734ae.webp 1024w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;progress.1055abbf6b48414c.webp 2048w&quot; class=&quot;Progress each week&quot; &#x2F;&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here you can see progress after each session (about 2 hours of painting time).&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</description>
